20. (1) An advertisement by any person for the supply of goods or
services by mail order shall contain—
(a) the name and licence number of such person;
(b) the address of such person, which address shall not be a
postal box number;
(c) the telephone number of such person;
(d) a detailed description of the goods offered or services to be
provided;
(e) the places and times where a sample of the goods may be
inspected;
(f) the prices of the goods or services;
(g) the cost of delivery, if any, and the manner of delivery, of
the goods; and
(h) the time when the goods or services could be expected to
be delivered or performed.
(2)  Any person who contravenes subsection (1) shall be guilty of
an offence.
Direct Sales and Anti-Pyramid Scheme                     23
Offence to furnish false information in advertisement
